{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775887188510,"sessionID":"ses_284e2dc29ffeH8EC4R1geNr7a3","part":{"id":"prt_d7b2001e4001BDKU57Vnc47Shl","messageID":"msg_d7b1f204e001222D7pzuB5ZtZF","sessionID":"ses_284e2dc29ffeH8EC4R1geNr7a3","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-b6612ee9db2643ba89b8ca69f51fcf89","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-033 — Makefile 构建目标体系\n\n## 概述\n\n| 属性 | 值 |\n|------|-----|\n| AR | AR-033 |\n| Module | root |\n| Language | Makefile |\n| Size | M |\n\n---\n\n## 1. Purpose (目的)\n\nEstablish a comprehensive Makefile build target system for AgentCube, providing:\n\n1. **Build Standardization**: Unified build interface across all binaries (workloadmanager, router, picod, agentd, agentctl, agentcube, agentsandbox)\n2. **Developer Ergonomics**: Short, memorable commands for common development tasks\n3. **CI/CD Integration**: Consistent targets for GitHub Actions workflows\n4. **Quality Gates**: Lint, test, coverage, and code generation verification targets\n5. **Cross-Platform Support**: Multi-architecture build support with configurable variables\n\n**Target Categories**:\n\n| Category | Targets | Purpose |\n|----------|---------|---------|\n| Build | `build`, `build-*`, `all` | Compile Go binaries |\n| Test | `test`, `test-coverage`, `e2e`, `e2e-clean` | Run unit, coverage, and E2E tests |\n| Quality | `lint`, `fmt`, `gen-check`, `copyright-check` | Code quality verification |\n| Docker | `docker-build-*`, `docker-buildx-*` | Container image builds |\n| Install | `install`, `install-*` | Install binaries to `$GOPATH/bin` or custom prefix |\n| Clean | `clean`, `clean-*` | Remove build artifacts |\n\n---\n\n## 2. Scope (范围)\n\n### 2.1 In Scope\n\n| Deliverable | Description |\n|-------------|-------------|\n| `Makefile` rewrite | Comprehensive target system with categorized build targets |\n| Binary targets | Individual targets for each binary: `build-workloadmanager`, `build-router`, `build-picod`, `build-agentd`, `build-agentctl`, `build-agentcube`, `build-agentsandbox` |\n| Test targets | `test` (unit tests), `test-coverage` (coverage with html report), `test-race` (race detector) |\n| E2E targets | `e2e`, `e2e-setup`, `e2e-clean` for Kind-based end-to-end testing |\n| Quality targets | `lint` (golangci-lint), `fmt` (go fmt), `vet` (go vet), `gen-check` (codegen verification) |\n| Install targets | `install` (all binaries), `install-workloadmanager`, etc. |\n| Docker targets | Preserve existing `docker-build-*`, `docker-buildx-*` targets |\n| Cross-compile targets | `build-linux-amd64`, `build-linux-arm64`, `build-darwin-amd64`, etc. |\n| Help target | `make help` with formatted target documentation |\n\n### 2.2 Binary Inventory\n\n| Binary | Source Path | Output | Description |\n|--------|-------------|--------|-------------|\n| `workloadmanager` | `./cmd/workloadmanager` | `bin/workloadmanager` | Workload manager HTTP server |\n| `router` | `./cmd/router` | `bin/router` | Session routing and reverse proxy |\n| `picod` | `./cmd/picod` | `bin/picod` | Local code execution daemon |\n| `agentd` | `./cmd/agentd` | `bin/agentd` | Idle cleanup controller |\n| `agentctl` | `./cmd/agentctl` | `bin/agentctl` | CLI tool for AgentCube |\n| `agentcube` | `./cmd/agentcube` | `bin/agentcube` | Main CLI binary |\n| `agentsandbox` | `./cmd/agentsandbox` | `bin/agentsandbox` | Sandbox management binary |\n\n### 2.3 Variable System\n\n| Variable | Default | Description |\n|----------|---------|-------------|\n| `IMAGE_REPO` | `ghcr.io/volcano-sh/agentcube` | Docker image repository |\n| `VERSION` | `git describe --tags --always --dirty` | Version tag for images |\n| `TARGETOS` | `linux` | Target OS for cross-compilation |\n| `TARGETARCH` | `amd64` | Target architecture |\n| `GO_VERSION` | `1.24` | Go version for CI alignment |\n| `GOLANGCI_LINT_VERSION` | `1.64.7` | golangci-lint version |\n| `BINDIR` | `bin/` | Output directory for binaries |\n| `INSTALL_PREFIX` | `$GOPATH/bin` | Installation prefix |\n\n### 2.4 Out of Scope\n\n| Item | Reason |\n|------|--------|\n| Python SDK targets | Python has separate `pyproject.toml` and `pytest` setup |\n| Helm chart targets | Covered by separate Helm tooling |\n| Release automation | Covered by `build-push-release.yml` workflow |\n| Makefile documentation beyond `help` target | External documentation in `docs/` |\n\n---\n\n## 3. Impact Analysis (影响分析)\n\n### 3.1 新增文件\n\n| File | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| N/A | No new files; Makefile will be enhanced |\n\n### 3.2 修改文件\n\n| File | Change |\n|------|--------|\n| `Makefile` | Major rewrite: add categorized targets, help system, cross-compile support |\n| `.github/workflows/*.yml` | Update to use new Make targets (e.g., `make lint` instead of inline commands) |\n\n### 3.3 Target Mapping (Current → New)\n\n| Current Target | New Target | Notes |\n|----------------|------------|-------|\n| `all` | `all` | Unchanged; depends on `build` |\n| `build` | `build` | Enhanced; builds all binaries |\n| N/A | `build-workloadmanager` | New single binary target |\n| N/A | `build-router` | New single binary target |\n| N/A | `build-picod` | New single binary target |\n| N/A | `build-agentd` | New single binary target |\n| `test` | `test` | Enhanced with verbose flag |\n| N/A | `test-coverage` | New coverage target |\n| N/A | `test-race` | New race detector target |\n| N/A | `e2e`, `e2e-clean` | New E2E test targets |\n| N/A | `lint` | New golangci-lint target |\n| N/A | `fmt`, `vet` | New formatting targets |\n| N/A | `gen-check` | New codegen verification target |\n| `docker-build` | `docker-build` | Unchanged |\n| `docker-build-router` | `docker-build-router` | Unchanged |\n| `docker-build-picod` | `docker-build-picod` | Unchanged |\n| `docker-build-all` | `docker-build-all` | Unchanged |\n| `docker-buildx-*` | `docker-buildx-*` | Unchanged |\n| `clean` | `clean` | Enhanced; cleans all artifacts |\n| N/A | `install`, `install-*` | New installation targets |\n| N/A | `help` | New help target |\n\n### 3.4 Upstream Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Purpose |\n|------------|---------|\n| `go` | Go toolchain (1.24+) |\n| `golangci-lint` | Linting tool |\n| `docker` | Container builds |\n| `docker buildx` | Multi-arch builds |\n| `kind` | E2E testing cluster |\n| `helm` | E2E chart deployment |\n| `git` | Version tagging |\n\n### 3.5 Downstream Consumers\n\n| Consumer | Usage |\n|----------|-------|\n| `CI: main.yml` | `make build` for build verification |\n| `CI: lint.yml` | `make lint` for golangci-lint |\n| `CI: test-coverage.yml` | `make test-coverage` for coverage |\n| `CI: e2e.yml` | `make e2e`, `make e2e-clean` |\n| `CI: codegen-check.yml` | `make gen-check` |\n| `CI: copyright-check.yml` | `make gen-copyright` |\n| `CI: build-push-release.yml` | `make docker-buildx-push-*` |\n| `E2E: run_e2e.sh` | `make docker-build`, `make docker-build-router`, `make docker-build-picod` |\n| Developers | `make help`, `make build`, `make test`, `make lint` |\n\n---\n\n## 4. Alternatives Considered (备选方案)\n\n### Alternative 1: Separate Makefiles per Component\n\n**Approach**: Create `Makefile` in each `cmd/` subdirectory.\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| Pros | Component isolation; independent builds |\n| Cons | Duplication; harder to manage cross-cutting concerns (lint, coverage); CI complexity |\n\n**Decision**: Rejected. Single root Makefile provides unified interface and simpler CI configuration.\n\n### Alternative 2: Just/Task/Earthly instead of Make\n\n**Approach**: Use modern task runners (Just, Task, Earthly) instead of GNU Make.\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| Pros | Modern syntax; better dependency management; Earthly provides containerized builds |\n| Cons | Additional tool dependency; team unfamiliarity; CI requires installation; GNU Make is ubiquitous |\n\n**Decision**: Rejected. GNU Make is universally available in CI environments and familiar to all developers.\n\n### Alternative 3: Shell Scripts for Complex Operations\n\n**Approach**: Keep Makefile minimal; use shell scripts for complex operations (E2E, codegen).\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| Pros | More programming flexibility; easier conditionals |\n| Cons | Multiple entry points; `make help` cannot document scripts; harder to maintain consistency |\n\n**Decision**: Partially adopted. E2E test script `run_e2e.sh` preserved; Makefile targets wrap the script for unified interface.\n\n### Alternative 4: No Cross-Compile Targets\n\n**Approach**: Rely solely on Docker buildx for multi-arch builds; no native cross-compile targets.\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| Pros | Simpler Makefile; Docker handles cross-compilation |\n| Cons | Slower iteration for cross-arch development; cannot test binaries without Docker |\n\n**Decision**: Rejected. Native cross-compile targets (`build-linux-arm64`, etc.) enable fast local testing without Docker overhead.\n\n### Alternative 5: Bazel/Buck Build System\n\n**Approach**: Adopt Bazel or Buck for hermetic, reproducible builds.\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| Pros | Deterministic builds; remote caching; advanced dependency management |\n| Cons | Significant migration effort; steep learning curve; overkill for current project scale |\n\n**Decision**: Rejected. Makefile + Go modules provides sufficient build reproducibility at current project scale.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Risks\n\n| Risk | Mitigation |\n|------|------------|\n| Makefile complexity growth | Organize targets by category; use `make help` for discoverability; document in comments |\n| Target naming inconsistency | Follow Go community conventions; use `kebab-case` for multi-word targets |\n| CI workflow divergence | CI workflows must reference Make targets, not inline commands |\n| Version drift between CI and Makefile | Use shared variables (`GO_VERSION`, `GOLANGCI_LINT_VERSION`); document in comments |\n| Race conditions in parallel builds | Use `.NOTPARALLEL` for sensitive targets; ensure `go build` handles parallelism |\n| Hidden dependencies | Use phony targets with explicit dependencies; document prerequisites |\n\n---\n\n## 6. Implementation Checklist\n\n- [ ] Add binary-specific build targets (`build-workloadmanager`, `build-router`, etc.)\n- [ ] Add `test-coverage` target with html report output\n- [ ] Add `test-race` target with race detector enabled\n- [ ] Add `lint` target using golangci-lint\n- [ ] Add `fmt` and `vet` targets\n- [ ] Add `gen-check` target for codegen verification\n- [ ] Add `gen-copyright` target for copyright headers\n- [ ] Add `e2e` and `e2e-clean` targets wrapping `test/e2e/run_e2e.sh`\n- [ ] Add `install` and `install-*` targets\n- [ ] Add cross-compile targets (`build-linux-amd64`, `build-linux-arm64`, etc.)\n- [ ] Add `help` target with formatted output\n- [ ] Organize targets into logical categories with comments\n- [ ] Update `.PHONY` declarations\n- [ ] Document variables with `?=` defaults\n- [ ] Verify CI workflows reference new targets\n- [ ] Test `make help` output is readable\n- [ ] Test all targets work on Linux and macOS\n\n---\n\n## 7. References\n\n- GNU Make Manual: https://www.gnu.org/software/make/manual/\n- Go Build Modes: https://go.dev/cmd/go/#hdr-Build_modes\n- golangci-lint: https://golangci-lint.run/\n- Kind (Kubernetes in Docker): https://kind.sigs.k8s.io/\n- GitHub Actions Makefile best practices: https://docs.github.com/en/actions/using-workflows/workflow-syntax-for-github-actions#jobsjob_idstepsshell\n- ci-cd/design.md — Existing workflow targets (lines 8-20)\n- deployment/design.md — Docker build targets\n- test/e2e/run_e2e.sh — E2E test orchestration","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-033/proposal.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-033/proposal.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-033/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775887188482,"end":1775887188507}}}}
